{"title_page": "Shohei Okuno", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2017}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Shohei Okuno\n| image               = Okuno while in Sloboda.png\n| caption             = Okuno while in Sloboda\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1990|8|18|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]\n| height              = {{height|m=1.78}}\n| position            = [[Midfielder (association football)|Midfielder]] / [[Striker (association football)|Striker]]\n| currentclub         = [[Albion Park White Eagles]]\n| clubnumber          = \n| youthyears1         = 2003\u20132006\n| youthclubs1         = [[Gamba Osaka]]\n| youthyears2         = 2006\u20132009\n| youthclubs2         = Kokoku Highschool\n| youthyears3         = 2009\u20132013\n| youthclubs3         = Hannan University\n| years1              = 2013\n| clubs1              = [[FK Auda|Auda R\u012bga]]\n| caps1               = 10\n| goals1              = 8\n| years2              = 2013\u20132014\n| clubs2              = [[FK Sloboda U\u017eice|Sloboda U\u017eice]]\n| caps2               = 29\n| goals2              = 1\n| years3              = 2014\n| clubs3              = [[Pogo\u0144 Szczecin]]\n| caps3               = 5\n| goals3              = 0\n| years4              = 2015\n| clubs4              = [[Bytovia Byt\u00f3w]]\n| caps4               = 7\n| goals4              = 0\n| years5              = 2016\u2013\n| clubs5              = [[Albion Park White Eagles]]\n| caps5               = 0\n| goals5              = 0\n| nationalyears1      = \n| nationalteam1       = \n| nationalcaps1       = \n| nationalgoals1      = \n| medaltemplates      = \n| club-update         = 1 January 2016\n| nationalteam-update = 1 January 2016\n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Shohei Okuno'''|\u5965\u91ce \u5c06\u5e73|Okuno Sh\u014dhei|born 18 August 1990}} is a [[Japanese people|Japanese]] [[Association football|footballer]] playing for [[Albion Park White Eagles]].\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[Tokyo]],<ref>[http://www.srbijafudbal.net/sloboda_uzice/okuno.htm Shohei Okuno] at Srbijafudbal</ref> he played with Latvian side [[FK Auda]]<ref>[http://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/shohei-okuno/ Shohei Okuno] at Worldfootball</ref> since 2013.  With Auda he played in the Latvian [[Latvian First League|1. Liga]] in the 2013 season. In summer 2013 he came to Serbia and after a successful trial he signed with top league side [[FK Sloboda U\u017eice]].<ref>[http://www.fksloboda.rs/prvitim.html 2013\u201314 squad] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130902022727/http://fksloboda.rs/prvitim.html |date=2 September 2013 }} at FK Sloboda U\u017eice official website, retrieved 28-8-2013</ref>  He joined Sloboda along with another Japanese player also coming from Latvia, [[Keisuke Ogawa]], who came from [[FC J\u016brmala]].  Shohei Okuno made his debut in the [[2013\u201314 Serbian SuperLiga]] in the second round match played on August 18, 2013, against [[FK \u010cukari\u010dki]].<ref name=\"soccerway\">[https://int.soccerway.com/players/okuno-shohei/309011/ Shohei Okuno] at Soccerway</ref> He scored his first goal for the club on 29 September 2013 against [[FK Radni\u010dki Kragujevac|Radni\u010dki 1923]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sportal.rs/news.php?news=110322 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-09-29 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140508062150/http://sportal.rs/news.php?news=110322 |archivedate=8 May 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nNext he move to Poland where he played with [[Pogo\u0144 Szczecin]] in the first half of the [[2014\u201315 Ekstraklasa]]. During winter-break he moved to another Polish club, [[Bytovia Byt\u00f3w]], playing in the [[I liga]].<ref name=\"soccerway\"/>\n\nDUring withre-break of the 2015\u201316 season, he left Poland and settled in Australia where he joined [[Albion Park White Eagles]].<ref>[http://www.90minut.pl/kariera.php?id=28054 Shohei Okuno] at 90minut.pl</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Okuno, Shohei}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Tokyo]]\n[[Category:Japanese footballers]]\n[[Category:Japanese expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:FK Auda players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Latvia]]\n[[Category:Japanese expatriate sportspeople in Latvia]]\n[[Category:FK Sloboda U\u017eice players]]\n[[Category:Serbian SuperLiga players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Serbia]]\n[[Category:Pogo\u0144 Szczecin players]]\n[[Category:Bytovia Byt\u00f3w players]]\n[[Category:Ekstraklasa players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Poland]]\n[[Category:Albion Park White Eagles players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate soccer players in Australia]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n\n\n{{Japan-footy-forward-1990s-stub}}\n{{Japan-footy-midfielder-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2017}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name                = Shohei Okuno\n| image               = Okuno while in Sloboda.png\n| caption             = Okuno while in Sloboda\n| birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1990|8|18|df=y}}\n| birth_place         = [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]\n| height              = {{height|m=1.78}}\n| position            = [[Midfielder (association football)|Midfielder]] / [[Striker (association football)|Striker]]\n| currentclub         = [[Albion Park White Eagles]]\n| clubnumber          = \n| youthyears1         = 2003\u20132006\n| youthclubs1         = [[Gamba Osaka]]\n| youthyears2         = 2006\u20132009\n| youthclubs2         = Kokoku Highschool\n| youthyears3         = 2009\u20132013\n| youthclubs3         = Hannan University\n| years1              = 2013\n| clubs1              = [[FK Auda|Auda R\u012bga]]\n| caps1               = 10\n| goals1              = 8\n| years2              = 2013\u20132014\n| clubs2              = [[FK Sloboda U\u017eice|Sloboda U\u017eice]]\n| caps2               = 29\n| goals2              = 1\n| years3              = 2014\n| clubs3              = [[Pogo\u0144 Szczecin]]\n| caps3               = 5\n| goals3              = 0\n| years4              = 2015\n| clubs4              = [[Bytovia Byt\u00f3w]]\n| caps4               = 7\n| goals4              = 0\n| years5              = 2016\u2013\n| clubs5              = [[Albion Park White Eagles]]\n| caps5               = 0\n| goals5              = 0\n| nationalyears1      = \n| nationalteam1       = \n| nationalcaps1       = \n| nationalgoals1      = \n| medaltemplates      = \n| club-update         = 1 January 2016\n| nationalteam-update = 1 January 2016\n}}\n{{Nihongo|'''Shohei Okuno'''|\u5965\u91ce \u5c06\u5e73|Okuno Sh\u014dhei|born 18 August 1990}} is a [[Japanese people|Japanese]] [[Association football|footballer]] playing for [[Albion Park White Eagles]].\n\n==Career==\nBorn in [[Tokyo]],<ref>[http://www.srbijafudbal.net/sloboda_uzice/okuno.htm Shohei Okuno] at Srbijafudbal</ref> he played with Latvian side [[FK Auda]]<ref>[http://www.worldfootball.net/player_summary/shohei-okuno/ Shohei Okuno] at Worldfootball</ref> since 2013.  With Auda he played in the Latvian [[Latvian First League|1. Liga]] in the 2013 season. In summer 2013 he came to Serbia and after a successful trial he signed with top league side [[FK Sloboda U\u017eice]].<ref>[http://www.fksloboda.rs/prvitim.html 2013\u201314 squad] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130902022727/http://fksloboda.rs/prvitim.html |date=2 September 2013 }} at FK Sloboda U\u017eice official website, retrieved 28-8-2013</ref>  He joined Sloboda along with another Japanese player also coming from Latvia, [[Keisuke Ogawa]], who came from [[FC J\u016brmala]].  Shohei Okuno made his debut in the [[2013\u201314 Serbian SuperLiga]] in the second round match played on August 18, 2013, against [[FK \u010cukari\u010dki]].<ref name=\"soccerway\">[https://int.soccerway.com/players/okuno-shohei/309011/ Shohei Okuno] at Soccerway</ref> He scored his first goal for the club on 29 September 2013 against [[FK Radni\u010dki Kragujevac|Radni\u010dki 1923]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://sportal.rs/news.php?news=110322 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-09-29 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140508062150/http://sportal.rs/news.php?news=110322 |archivedate=8 May 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nNext he move to Poland where he played with [[Pogo\u0144 Szczecin]] in the first half of the [[2014\u201315 Ekstraklasa]]. During winter-break he moved to another Polish club, [[Bytovia Byt\u00f3w]], playing in the [[I liga]].<ref name=\"soccerway\"/>\n\nDUring withre-break of the 2015\u201316 season, he left Poland and settled in Australia where he joined [[Albion Park White Eagles]].<ref>[http://www.90minut.pl/kariera.php?id=28054 Shohei Okuno] at 90minut.pl</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Okuno, Shohei}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Tokyo]]\n[[Category:Japanese footballers]]\n[[Category:Japanese expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:FK Auda players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Latvia]]\n[[Category:Japanese expatriate sportspeople in Latvia]]\n[[Category:FK Sloboda U\u017eice players]]\n[[Category:Serbian SuperLiga players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Serbia]]\n[[Category:Pogo\u0144 Szczecin players]]\n[[Category:Bytovia Byt\u00f3w players]]\n[[Category:Ekstraklasa players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Poland]]\n[[Category:Albion Park White Eagles players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate soccer players in Australia]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n\n\n{{Japan-footy-forward-stub}}\n{{Japan-footy-midfielder-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Joeykai", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shohei_Okuno"}
