{"title_page": "Sho Yamamoto", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n|name                = Sho Yamamoto\n|image               =\n|fullname            = \n|birth_date          = {{birth date and age|1996|11|12|df=y}}\n|birth_place         = [[Tokyo]], [[Japan]]\n|height              = {{Height|m=1.80}}\n|currentclub         = [[FK Iskra Danilovgrad|Iskra Danilovgrad]]<br>(on loan from [[FK Spartak Subotica|Spartak Subotica]])\n|clubnumber          = 19\n|position            = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]]\n|youthclubs1         = [[FK Cetinje]]\n|youthyears1         = {{0|0000}}\u20132016\n|years1              = 2016\u20132017 |clubs1 = [[FK Rudar Pljevlja|Rudar Pljevlja]]               |caps1 = 15 |goals1 = 2\n|years2              = 2017\u20132019 |clubs2 = [[OFK Petrovac]]                                   |caps2 = 47 |goals2 = 7\n|years3              = 2019\u2013     |clubs3 = [[FK Spartak Subotica|Spartak Subotica]]           |caps3 = 2  |goals3 = 0\n|years4              = 2020\u2013     |clubs4 = \u2192 [[FK Iskra Danilovgrad|Iskra Danilovgrad]] (loan)|caps4 =    |goals4 =  \n|nationalyears1      = \n|nationalteam1       = \n|nationalcaps1       = \n|nationalgoals1      = \n|club-update         = 21 March 2020\n|nationalteam-update = \n}}\n\n{{nihongo|'''Sho Yamamoto'''|\u5c71\u672c \u5968|Yamamoto Sho|born 12 November 1996}} is a [[Japan]]ese [[Association football|footballer]] playing as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[FK Iskra Danilovgrad|Iskra Danilovgrad]], on loan from [[FK Spartak Subotica|Spartak Subotica]].\n\n==Career==\nBorn in Japanese capital [[Tokyo]], Yamamoto debuted professionally already abroad in Europe with [[FK Rudar Pljevlja]] in the [[2016\u201317 Montenegrin First League]]. He will play the following two seasons with another Montenegrin top-flight side, [[OFK Petrovac]]. His successful adaptation to football in former-Yugoslavia made him come up on the radars of other teams from the region, which resulted in his move in summer 2019 to Serbian side [[FK Spartak Subotica]].<ref>[http://www.srbijafudbal.com/zlatibor_voda/yamamoto.htm Sho Yamamoto] at srbijafudbal.com, retrieved 30-10-2019 {{in lang|sr}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n{{updated|19 August 2019.}}<ref>{{Soccerway|sho-yamamoto/464634|accessdate=19 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n!Apps\n!Goals\n|-\n|[[FK Rudar Pljevlja|Rudar Pljevlja]]\n|[[2016\u201317 Montenegrin First League|2016\u201317]]\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Montenegrin First League]]\n|15||2||2<ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"MC\">Appearances in the [[Montenegrin Cup]]</ref>||0||0||0||17||2\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[OFK Petrovac]]\n|[[2017\u201318 Montenegrin First League|2017\u201318]]\n|17||0||0||0||2<ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"MFLP/O\">Appearances in the Montenegrin First League playoffs</ref>||0||19||0\n|-\n|[[2018\u201319 Montenegrin First League|2018\u201319]]\n|30||7||4<ref group=\"lower-alpha\" name=\"MC\"/>||0||0||0||34||7\n|-\n! colspan=2 | Total\n!47!!7!!4!!0!!2!!0!!53!!7\n|-\n|[[FK Spartak Subotica|Spartak Subotica]]\n|[[2019\u201320 Serbian SuperLiga|2019\u201320]]\n|[[Serbian SuperLiga]]\n|2||0||0||0||0||0||2||0\n|-\n! colspan=3 | Career total\n!64!!9!!6!!0!!2!!0!!72!!9\n|}\n;Notes\n{{Reflist|group=lower-alpha}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{FK Spartak Subotica squad}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Yamamoto, Sho}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1996 births]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Tokyo]]\n[[Category:Japanese footballers]]\n[[Category:Japanese expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football forwards]]\n[[Category:Montenegrin First League players]]\n[[Category:Serbian SuperLiga players]]\n[[Category:FK Rudar Plj