{"title_page": "Lee Collins (footballer, born 1988)", "text_new": "{{other people|Lee Collins}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2012}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name        = Lee Collins\n| image       = Lee Collins.JPG\n| image_size  = 200\n| caption     = Collins playing for [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]] in 2010\n| fullname    = Lee Harvey Collins<ref>{{Hugman|22632|accessdate=9 March 2017}}</ref>\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1988|9|28|df=y}}<ref name=\"port-vale.co.uk\">{{cite web|url=http://www.port-vale.co.uk/page/ProfilesDetail/0,,10381~38222,00.html|title=Name: Lee Collins|work=port-vale.co.uk|accessdate=13 September 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110902054140/http://www.port-vale.co.uk/page/ProfilesDetail/0,,10381~38222,00.html|archive-date=2 September 2011|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Telford]], England<ref>{{soccerbase|46038|Lee Collins}}</ref>\n| height      = {{height|ft=5|in=11}}<ref name=\"port-vale.co.uk\" />\n| position    = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| currentclub = [[Yeovil Town F.C.|Yeovil Town]]\n| clubnumber  = 4\n| youthyears1 = 2004\u20132007\n| youthclubs1 = [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]]\n| years1 = 2007\u20132009 | clubs1 = [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] | caps1 = 0   | goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2007\u20132008 | clubs2 = \u2192 [[Hereford United F.C.|Hereford United]] (loan)        | caps2 = 16  | goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2008      | clubs3 = \u2192 [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]] (loan)                    | caps3 = 22  | goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2009\u20132012 | clubs4 = [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]]                             | caps4 = 120 | goals4 = 4\n| years5 = 2012      | clubs5 = \u2192 [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]] (loan)                      | caps5 = 7   | goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2012\u20132013 | clubs6 = [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]]                               | caps6 = 0   | goals6 = 0\n| years7 = 2012      | clubs7 = \u2192 [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]] (loan)        | caps7 = 8   | goals7 = 0\n| years8 = 2013\u20132015 | clubs8 = [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]]               | caps8 = 74  | goals8 = 1\n| years9 = 2015\u20132017 | clubs9 = [[Mansfield Town F.C.|Mansfield Town]]                   | caps9 = 72  | goals9 = 0\n| years10= 2017\u20132019 | clubs10 = [[Forest Green Rovers F.C.|Forest Green Rovers]]        | caps10= 54  | goals10= 3\n| years11= 2019\u2013     | clubs11 = [[Yeovil Town F.C.|Yeovil Town]]                        | caps11= 27  | goals11= 0\n| club-update = 17:08, 7 March 2020 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Lee Harvey Collins''' (born 28 September 1988) is an English professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[National League (division)|National League]] side [[Yeovil Town F.C.|Yeovil Town]]. He is more comfortable as a [[Defender (association football)#Centre back|centre-back]], but can also play as a [[Defender (association football)#Full back|full-back]].\n\nHe graduated through the [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] Academy to turn professional in February 2007. He spent much of the 2007\u201308 season on loan at [[Hereford United F.C.|Hereford United]], helping the club to win promotion into [[EFL League One|League One]]. He joined Port Vale on loan at the start of the 2008\u201309 season, and his loan stay was made permanent in January 2009. He played 53 games for the club in 2009\u201310, and continued to be a key member of the defence in 2010\u201311. He joined [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]] on loan in March 2012, with a view to a permanent deal in the summer. From Barnsley, he was loaned out to [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]] in September 2012. He moved on to [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]] in February 2013, and spent over two years with the club before moving on to [[Mansfield Town F.C.|Mansfield Town]]. He signed with [[Forest Green Rovers F.C.|Forest Green Rovers]] in May 2017 and stayed with the club for two seasons before joining non-league Yeovil Town in June 2019.\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Wolverhampton Wanderers===\nBorn in [[Telford]], [[Shropshire]], Collins was promoted to [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]]' first team squad for the first time in January 2007, signing his first professional forms the next month.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/w/wolverhampton_wanderers/6401195.stm|title=Academy stars rewarded by Wolves |date=27 February 2007|work=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=7 June 2009}}</ref> Though regularly on the bench, he never made a first team appearance. However, he played regularly for the club at reserve level and with the under-18s, for whom he was [[captain (association football)|captain]].\n\nHe joined [[Hereford United F.C.|Hereford United]] on 14 November 2007 on an initial month's loan,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/h/hereford_united/7094634.stm|title=Hereford recruit Wolves defender |date=14 November 2007|work=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=7 June 2009}}</ref> and made his league debut on 17 November 2007 in a 3\u20132 win at [[Stockport County F.C.|Stockport County]]. After impressing, his loan was extended to the end of the season,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/h/hereford_united/7148378.stm|title=Collins extends stay at Hereford|date=23 January 2008|work=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=7 June 2009}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/h/hereford_united/7232553.stm|title=Collins enjoying Bulls loan spell |date=7 February 2008|work=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=7 June 2009}}</ref> during which Hereford won promotion to [[EFL League One|League One]].\n[[File:Lee Collins4.JPG|thumb|right|200px|Collins at [[Vale Park]] in a 1\u20130 September 2010 victory over [[Aldershot Town F.C.|Aldershot Town]].]]\n\n===Port Vale===\nCollins went on loan to [[EFL League Two|League Two]] side [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]] at the start of the [[2008\u201309 Port Vale F.C. season|2008\u201309 season]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/p/port_vale/7534933.stm|title=Collins makes Valiants loan move |date=31 July 2008|work=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=7 June 2009}}</ref> and became a first team regular. Vale then signed him on a {{frac|2|1|2}}-year deal on 16 January 2009 after \"Wolves\" agreed to release him from the rest of his deal at [[Molineux Stadium|Molineux]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thewonderofyou.co.uk/news/Breaking-news--Brammer-and-Collins-sign.aspx|title=Breaking news: Brammer and Collins sign|date=16 January 2009|work=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]]|accessdate=16 January 2009}}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport2/hi/football/teams/p/port_vale/7833268.stm|title=Collins and Brammer sign for Vale |date=16 January 2009|work=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=7 June 2009}}</ref> He gained his first senior goal in a 1\u20131 home draw with [[Wycombe Wanderers F.C.|Wycombe Wanderers]] on 25 April 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thisisstaffordshire.co.uk/portvale/Match-Report-Port-Vale-1-Wycombe-1/article-936901-detail/article.html|title=Match Report: Port Vale 1 Wycombe 1|last=Shaw|first=Steve|date=25 April 2009|work=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]]|accessdate=25 April 2009}}</ref> With 42 appearances to his name in his first season with the club, he was described as the most consistent performer of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thisisstaffordshire.co.uk/portvale/Port-Vale-Match-stats/article-959501-detail/article.html|title=Port Vale: Match stats|date=4 May 2009|work=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]]|accessdate=4 May 2009}}</ref>\n\nHe remained in the first team for the start of the [[2009\u201310 Port Vale F.C. season|2009\u201310]] campaign. He was transfer listed in late September, along with the entire Port Vale squad, after manager [[Micky Adams]] saw his team slip to a third consecutive defeat.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/p/port_vale/8277136.stm|title=Adams puts Vale squad up for sale |date=27 September 2009|work=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=27 September 2009}}</ref> Despite this he remained a key member of the defence, alongside [[Gareth Owen (footballer, born 1982)|Gareth Owen]] and [[John McCombe]]. Playing regular football helped Collins realize that he needed to 'bulk out' to become a more physically dominant player.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/p/port_vale/8406423.stm|title=Port Vale defender Lee Collins wants to 'bulk out' |date=10 December 2009|work=[[BBC Sport]]|accessdate=10 December 2009}}</ref> His solid performances attracted attention, as well as March 2010 rumours of a \u00a3200,000 move to [[Watford F.C.|Watford]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2010/mar/12/football-transfer-rumours-rooney-real-madrid|title= transfer rumours: Wayne Rooney to Real Madrid?|date=12 March 2010|work=The Guardian|accessdate=13 March 2010}}</ref> Rumours that Collins rubbished as \"paper talk\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thisisstaffordshire.co.uk/portvale/Port-Vale-Collins-shrugs-transfer-talk/article-1929480-detail/article.html|title=Port Vale: Collins shrugs off transfer talk|date=20 March 2010|work=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]]|accessdate=20 March 2010}}</ref> A candidate for [[Port Vale F.C. Player of the Year|Player of the Year]], he instead picked up Chairman's Player of the Year and Players' Player of the Year awards, as well as the award for Best Assist \"following his storming run from inside his own half to set up [[Marc Richards]] against [[Hereford United F.C.|Hereford]] at [[Vale Park]]\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thisisstaffordshire.co.uk/news/Port-Vale-Griffith-takes-home-accolade/article-2145856-detail/article.html|title=Port Vale: Griffith takes home top accolade|last=Owen|first=Jon|date=12 May 2010|work=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]]|accessdate=12 May 2010}}</ref> Collins was keen to extend his contract beyond its conclusion in the summer of 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thisisstaffordshire.co.uk/news/Port-Vale-Collins-keen-extend-Vale-stay/article-2184130-detail/article.html|title=Port Vale: Collins keen to extend Vale stay|last=Shaw|first=Steve|date=21 May 2010|work=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]]|accessdate=21 May 2010}}</ref>\n\nHe got the perfect start to the [[2010\u201311 Port Vale F.C. season|2010\u201311 season]] by blasting in the only goal of the opening game of the season at [[Bury F.C.|Bury]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thisisstaffordshire.co.uk/news/Match-report-Bury-0-Port-Vale-1/article-2502539-detail/article.html|title=Match report: Bury 0 Port Vale 1|last=Shaw|first=Steve|date=7 August 2010|work=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]]|accessdate=7 August 2010}}</ref> Anticipating interest from other clubs, in September Adams began negotiations to extend his contract by a further season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thisisstaffordshire.co.uk/news/Port-Vale-Adams-set-open-talks-new-Collins-deal/article-2650928-detail/article.html|title=Port Vale: Micky Adams set to open talks on new Collins deal|last=Shaw|first=Steve|date=16 September 2010|work=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]]|accessdate=16 September 2010}}</ref> Upon signing the deal Collins praised current and former training staff at the club, naming [[Dean Glover]], [[Lee Sinnott]], [[Mark Grew]], [[Geoff Horsfield]], and Micky Adams as people who helped his progress 'massively'.<ref name=\"mass\">{{Cite web|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/p/port_vale/9034232.stm|title=Lee Collins and Stuart Tomlinson agree Port Vale deals |accessdate=30 May 2011|date=27 September 2010|work=[[BBC Sport]]}}</ref> His consistency over his 48 appearances helped Vale to boast one of the strongest defensive records in the division that season.\n\nHe missed a few weeks at the start of the [[2011\u201312 Port Vale F.C. season|2011\u201312 season]] after undergoing a small operation to repair a [[hernia]]-related problem.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.port-vale.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10381~2443159,00.html|title=Operation for Collins|date=6 September 2011|work=port-vale.co.uk|accessdate=7 September 2011}}{{Dead link|date=September 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> He was then sidelined for a further five weeks after he had to undergo surgery on an unrelated groin injury.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.port-vale.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10381~2469477,00.html|title=Collins to Have Operation|date=1 October 2011|work=port-vale.co.uk|accessdate=1 October 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111003004607/http://www.port-vale.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10381~2469477,00.html|archive-date=3 October 2011|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Vale conceded eighteen goals in the twelve games that Collins missed,<ref>{{cite news|title=Lee Collins injury return boosts Port Vale - Mark Grew|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/15639062.stm|accessdate=8 November 2011|newspaper=[[BBC Sport]]|date=8 November 2011}}</ref> before keeping a clean sheet on his return to the first team on 12 November, a goalless draw with [[Grimsby Town F.C.|Grimsby Town]] in the [[FA Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Port Vale   0 - 0   Grimsby|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/15604898.stm|accessdate=26 December 2011|newspaper=[[BBC Sport]]|date=12 November 2011}}</ref> He again was sidelined in January, as he picked up an ankle injury.<ref>{{cite news|last=Questier|first=Joe|title=Team News: Vale v AFC Wimbledon|url=http://www.port-vale.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10381~2574774,00.html|accessdate=21 January 2012|newspaper=port-vale.co.uk|date=13 January 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120124003605/http://www.port-vale.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10381~2574774,00.html|archive-date=24 January 2012|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In total he made 162 appearances for Vale, scoring four goals.<ref>{{cite news|title=Reds set to raid cash-strapped Vale for Collins|url=http://www.barnsley-chronicle.co.uk/sport/article/5023/reds-set-to-raid-cash-strapped-vale-for-collins|accessdate=15 March 2012|newspaper=Barnsley Chronicle|date=14 March 2012}}</ref> Collins was named as Port Vale's best left-back of the 2010s in a public poll taken in January 2020 by ''[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]]''; he received 50% of the vote, ahead of [[Carl Dickinson]] (40%).<ref>{{cite news |last1=Baggaley |first1=Michael |title=Results revealed as Port Vale fans vote for left back in Team of The Decade |url=https://www.stokesentinel.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/results-revealed-port-vale-fans-3712271 |accessdate=7 January 2020 |work=Stoke Sentinel |date=7 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Barnsley===\nOn 15 March 2012, Collins joined [[Barnsley F.C.|Barnsley]] on loan for the remainder of the season, with the move becoming permanent at the end of the season.<ref>{{cite news |title=Barnsley complete signing of Lee Collins from Port Vale |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/17369649|accessdate=15 March 2012|publisher=[[BBC Sport]]|date=15 March 2012}}</ref> Port Vale received \u00a350,000 for the loan deal.<ref>{{cite news|title=Port Vale: Vale to pocket \u00a350,000 for loanee Lee Collins|url=http://www.thisisstaffordshire.co.uk/Port-Vale-Vale-pocket-pound-50-000-loanee-Lee/story-15521437-detail/story.html|accessdate=15 March 2012|newspaper=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]]|date=15 March 2012}}</ref> He arrived at [[Oakwell]] in the midst of an injury crisis in the Barnsley defence.<ref>{{cite news|last=Goulding|first=Neil|title=Collins just the man says Hill|url=http://www.thestar.co.uk/sport/football/barnsley/collins-just-the-man-says-hill-1-4346422|accessdate=15 March 2012|newspaper=The Star|date=15 March 2012}}</ref> He impressed manager [[Keith Hill (footballer)|Keith Hill]] in his seven appearances in [[2011\u201312 Barnsley F.C. season|2011\u201312]], particularly in the game against [[Blackpool F.C.|Blackpool]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Collins Completes Reds Switch|url=http://www.barnsleyfc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10309~2764687,00.html|archive-url=https://archive.is/20120720202219/http://www.barnsleyfc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10309~2764687,00.html|url-status=dead|archive-date=20 July 2012|work=barnsleyfc.co.uk|accessdate=10 May 2012}}</ref>\n\nDespite injuries to other \"Tykes\" defenders, he did not feature in the first team at the start of the [[2012\u201313 Barnsley F.C. season|2012\u201313 season]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Barnsley's Lee Collins joins Shrewsbury Town on loan|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/19756287|accessdate=28 September 2012|newspaper=[[BBC Sport]]|date=28 September 2012}}</ref> On 28 September 2012, Collins joined League One side [[Shrewsbury Town F.C.|Shrewsbury Town]] on a month-long loan deal.<ref name=\"Defender Joins\">{{cite web|title=Defender Joins On Loan|url=http://www.shrewsburytown.com/news/article/29sep12-defender-joins-on-loan-395072.aspx|work=shrewsburytown.com|accessdate=28 September 2012}}</ref> \"Shrews\" boss [[Graham Turner]], his former manager at Hereford, said that he would provide valuable defensive experience and cover following an injury to [[Joe Jacobson]].<ref name=\"Defender Joins\"/> Collins made eight appearances before he had his loan deal extended by one month.<ref>{{cite news|title=Shrewsbury Town extend Lee Collins loan from Barnsley|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/20141872|accessdate=3 November 2012|newspaper=[[BBC Sport]]|date=30 October 2012}}</ref> On 29 November, his loan was cut short and he returned to his parent club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/20540230|title=Shrewsbury Town end Lee Collins and Julian Bennett loan deals|publisher=BBC Sport|date=29 November 2012 |accessdate=29 November 2012}}</ref> Having never taken to the field for Barnsley in the [[2012\u201313 Barnsley F.C. season|2012\u201313 season]], he was released from his contract on 31 January 2013 by manager [[David Flitcroft]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Barnsley sign Rory Delap and Chris O'Grady as Mido leaves|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/21280588|accessdate=31 January 2013|newspaper=[[BBC Sport]]|date=31 January 2013}}</ref>\n\n===Northampton Town===\n[[File:Lee Collins 16-08-2014 1.jpg|thumb|200px|Collins playing for [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]] in 2014]]\nHe joined [[Northampton Town F.C.|Northampton Town]] until the end of the [[2012\u201313 Northampton Town F.C. season|2012\u201313 season]] in February 2013.<ref name=\"free transfer\">{{cite news|title=Lee Collins: Northampton sign defender on free transfer|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/21381532|accessdate=8 February 2013|newspaper=[[BBC Sport]]|date=8 February 2013}}</ref> Manager [[Aidy Boothroyd]] signed him to provide competition in the \"Cobblers\" defence, particularly to left-back [[Joe Widdowson]].<ref name=\"free transfer\"/> On 20 April, he scored an own goal at [[Vale Park]] which effectively promoted his former club, [[Port Vale F.C.|Port Vale]], back into League One.<ref>{{cite news|title=Port Vale 2 - 2 Northampton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/22133274|accessdate=21 April 2013|newspaper=[[BBC Sport]]|date=20 April 2013}}</ref> He was allowed to participate in the play-offs, despite being subject to a curfew order.<ref>{{cite news|title=Northampton Town hope Lee Collins can play despite curfew|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/22298768|accessdate=25 April 2013|newspaper=[[BBC Sport]]|date=25 April 2013}}</ref> He played 55 minutes of the [[2013 Football League Two play-off Final|play-off final]] defeat to [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Bradford 3 - 0 Northampton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/22491339|accessdate=18 May 2013|newspaper=[[BBC Sport]]|date=18 May 2013}}</ref> He signed a new two-year contract in May 2013.<ref>{{cite news|last=Bazeley|first=Marc|title=Aidy Boothroyd hopes Lee Collins can help Northampton Town to promotion|url=http://www.northampton-news-hp.co.uk/Sport/Cobblers/Football-Aidy-Boothroyd-hopes-Lee-Collins-can-help-Northampton-Town-to-promotion-20130524160000.htm|accessdate=23 June 2013|newspaper=Herald and Post|date=24 May 2013|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130624220404/http://www.northampton-news-hp.co.uk/Sport/Cobblers/Football-Aidy-Boothroyd-hopes-Lee-Collins-can-help-Northampton-Town-to-promotion-20130524160000.htm|archive-date=24 June 2013|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nHe played 25 games during the [[2013\u201314 Northampton Town F.C. season|2013\u201314]] campaign as Northampton avoided relegation out of the [[English Football League]] by a three-point margin, though played only twice under new manager [[Chris Wilder]] after he was ruled out for the rest of the season with a foot tendon injury in February.<ref>{{cite news|title=Lee Collins: Northampton Town skipper out for rest of season|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/26265358|accessdate=4 May 2014|newspaper=[[BBC Sport]]|date=20 February 2014}}</ref> During the season, he was appointed as club captain.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lake|first1=Jefferson|title=Toe injury rules Cobblers captain Collins out of Torquay trip|url=http://www.northamptonchron.co.uk/sport/toe-injury-rules-cobblers-captain-collins-out-of-torquay-trip-1-5868308|accessdate=5 August 2014|work=Northampton Chronicle & Echo|date=10 February 2014}}</ref> He made 43 appearances in the [[2014\u201315 Northampton Town F.C. season|2014\u201315]] campaign but was not offered a new contract in the summer as Wilder opted to use [[Zander Diamond]] and [[Ryan Cresswell]] as his new centre-back partnership.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Thomas|first1=Ciaran|title=Lee Collins' release the 'toughest' decision for Chris Wilder during player cull|url=http://www.northampton-news-hp.co.uk/Northampton-Town-Lee-Collins-release-toughest/story-26440837-detail/story.html|accessdate=9 May 2015|work=Northants Herald and Post|date=5 May 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150518073337/http://www.northampton-news-hp.co.uk/Northampton-Town-Lee-Collins-release-toughest/story-26440837-detail/story.html|archive-date=18 May 2015|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n===Mansfield Town===\nCollins joined League Two club [[Mansfield Town F.C.|Mansfield Town]] in June 2015, with \"Stags\" manager [[Adam Murray]] praising his ability and experience, saying that \"To bring Lee in to the building is a big one for us\".<ref>{{cite news|title=Lee Collins: Mansfield Town sign Northampton Town defender|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/33054735|accessdate=9 June 2015|work=[[BBC Sport]]|date=8 June 2015}}</ref> He made 38 appearances across the [[2015\u201316 Mansfield Town F.C. season|2015\u201316]] campaign after recovering from a foot injury picked up in pre-season.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lomas|first1=John|title=Big Mansfield Town chance at last for patient Lee Collins |url=http://www.chad.co.uk/sport/mansfield-town/mansfield-town-news/big-mansfield-town-chance-at-last-for-patient-lee-collins-1-7476926|accessdate=22 May 2016|work=Chad|date=25 September 2015}}</ref> He was appointed club captain in January and went on to sign a new contract in the summer.<ref>{{cite news|title=Lee Collins, Krystian Pearce & Mal Benning sign Mansfield Town deals|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36320548|accessdate=22 May 2016|work=BBC Sport|date=18 May 2016}}</ref> He was released by Mansfield at the end of the [[2016\u201317 Mansfield Town F.C. season|2016\u201317]] season, having made 44 appearances to help Mansfield to a 12th-place finish.<ref>{{cite web|title=Matt Green: Mansfield striker among 11 released by Stags|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/39874652|website=BBC Sport|accessdate=10 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n===Forest Green Rovers===\nIn May 2017, Collins joined [[Forest Green Rovers F.C.|Forest Green Rovers]] on a two-year contract to become the club's first signing following their promotion from the [[National League (English football)|National League]] into the English Football League.<ref>{{Cite web| url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/39965708 |title=Lee Collins: Forest Green Rovers sign Mansfield Town defender on free transfer |publisher=BBC Sport |date=18 May 2017 |accessdate=21 May 2017}}</ref> He scored two goals in 48 appearances over the [[2017\u201318 Forest Green Rovers F.C. season|2017\u201318]] campaign to help the Green to a 21st-place finish. He missed much of the [[2018\u201319 Forest Green Rovers F.C. season|2018\u201319]] season with a long-term injury, but returned to fitness in time to feature in both legs of the play-off semi-final defeat to [[Tranmere Rovers F.C.|Tranmere Rovers]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Port |first1=Henry |title=The clever Forest Green tactic that worked in vital victory |url=https://www.gloucestershirelive.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/clever-forest-green-rovers-tactic-2786887 |accessdate=14 May 2019 |work=gloucestershirelive |date=23 April 2019}}</ref> He was released by Forest Green Rovers at the end of the 2018\u201319 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/48283356|title=Forest Green Rovers retained list: Reuben Reid transfer-listed as eight are released|date=15 May 2019|accessdate=20 May 2019|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref>\n\n===Yeovil Town===\nOn 26 June 2019, Collins signed a two-year contract with newly-relegated [[National League (division)|National League]] side [[Yeovil Town F.C.|Yeovil Town]]; manager [[Darren Sarll]] said that \"Lee is a winner and his experience and leadership will make him a big part of this squad\".<ref>{{cite news |last1=Evans |first1=Daniel |title=Forest Green Rovers defender is Yeovil Town's third Summer signing |url=https://www.somersetlive.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/lee-collins-becomes-yeovil-towns-3023390 |accessdate=27 June 2019 |work=somersetlive |date=26 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nCollins was called up to the [[England national under-19 football team|England under-19s]], but did not earn a cap. Despite this he does not rule out one day playing for the [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]], who he qualifies for through his [[Irish people|Irish]] father.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thewonderofyou.co.uk/news/Vale-was-the-right-move-for-new-recruit-Collins.aspx|title=Vale was the right move for new recruit Collins|date=31 January 2009|work=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]]|accessdate=31 January 2009|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20100516183017/http://www.thewonderofyou.co.uk/news/Vale-was-the-right-move-for-new-recruit-Collins.aspx|archivedate=16 May 2010|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==Style of play==\nCollins can play anywhere in defence, though prefers to play at [[Defender (association football)#Centre back|centre-back]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Hill: Collins has the \"right ingredients\" to be a success\"|url=http://www.barnsleyfc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10309~2659558,00.html|accessdate=15 March 2012|newspaper=barnsleyfc.co.uk|date=15 March 2012}}{{Dead link|date=September 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> Port Vale manager [[Micky Adams]] claimed that Collins always gave his all in training, and was a \"remarkable athlete... [in] terms of fitness.\"<ref name=\"talent\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thisisstaffordshire.co.uk/portvale/Port-Vale-Richards-predicts-big-things-team-mate-Collins/article-1785928-detail/article.html|title=Port Vale: Richards predicts big things for team-mate Collins|last=Shaw|first=Steve|date=2 February 2010|work=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]]|accessdate=2 February 2010}}</ref> In February 2010, teammate [[Marc Richards]] said that \"he reads the game well, he's fast, he's strong...[and has] strength and pace, and he's got vision as well.\"<ref name=\"talent\" />\n\n==Personal life==\nCollins attended [[Thomas Telford School]] as a youth, alongside fellow professionals such as [[Elliott Bennett]] and [[Danny Guthrie]]. Also attending the school was future Port Vale teammate [[Sam Morsy]]. His partner Rachel gave birth to their daughters, Amelia-Grace, on 15 December 2010, Laila-Rose on 14 March 2016 and Charley-Mae in August 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thisisstaffordshire.co.uk/news/Port-Vale-Collins-hopes-greater-responsibilities-benefit-club/article-3158857-detail/article.html|title=Port Vale: Collins hopes greater responsibilities will benefit club|last=Shaw|first=Steve|date=29 January 2011|work=[[The Sentinel (Staffordshire)|The Sentinel]]|accessdate=29 January 2011}}</ref>\n\nCollins was convicted for assault in April 2013 after punching and kicking a man in [[Shropshire]] the previous year, and was given a two-year suspended prison sentence.<ref>{{cite news|title=Pub fight footballer Lee Collins gets suspended prison sentence|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-northamptonshire-22281376|accessdate=25 April 2013|newspaper=[[BBC Sport]]|date=24 April 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n\n[[File:Lee Collins 03-08-2013 1.jpg|thumb|200px|Collins playing for Northampton Town in 2013]]\n{{updated|7 March 2020.}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[FA Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|[[EFL Cup|League Cup]]\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]]||[[2007\u201308 Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C. season|2007\u201308]]<ref name=\"07/08\">{{Soccerbase season|id=46038|season=2007|accessdate=1 January 2